This paper discusses the use of predictive models in decision-making and proposes a new approach to learning decision policies that maximize utility under fairness constraints. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on learning decision policies, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
